Interface Embedding<NodeType,EdgeType>

Type Parameters:
NodeType - the type of the node labels (will be hashed and checked with .equals(..))
EdgeType - the type of the edge labels (will be hashed and checked with .equals(..))
All Superinterfaces:
Frequented, Generic<NodeType,EdgeType>, java.io.Serializable
All Known Implementing Classes:
DAGmEmbedding, GSpanEmbedding, HPEmbeddingWrapper
public interface Embedding<NodeType,EdgeType>
extends Generic<NodeType,EdgeType>, Frequented, java.io.Serializable

This interface declares the functionality of an embedding between a subgraph and its supergraph An embedding maps each node and each edge of a subgraph to exactly one edge of the supergraph

Author:
Marc Woerlein (woerlein@informatik.uni-erlangen.de)
